text: Santa Rosa is a city in and the county seat of Sonoma County, California, United States. At the 2020 census its population was 178,127. In the beginning of October, 2017, a firestorm burnt 5% of the homes in the city, killing atleast 19 people. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:Settlements in Sonoma County, California Category:Cities in California Category:Cities in the San Francisco Bay Area Category:County seats in California
title: Santa Rosa, California
